    <h2 class="head2">prepared by: Rameshwor Rawal</h2>
    <img src="https://images.pixexid.com/a-bowl-of-spaghetti-wf695vvg.jpeg" alt="">
</header>
<main class="main">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="left-side">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Spaghetti pasta</li>
                <li>Eggs</li>
                <li>pancetta or bacon</li>
                <li>Grated parmesan</li>
                <li>black pepper</li>
                <li>Garlic</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="right-side">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <p>Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Fry pancetta or bacon until crispy.</li>
            <li>In a bowl, whisk eggs, Parmesan cheese, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Once spaghetti is cooked, drain and immediately add to the pan with pancetta.</li>
            <li>Remove from heat and quickly mix in the egg mixture until the eggs thicken but do not scramble.</li>
            <li>Serve immediately, garnished with extra Parmesan and black pepper.</li>
            
          </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom">
